node.text: This video scared the crap out of me and made me relive some of the scary moments I was just discussing with a friend about some very similar personal experiences that I've dealt with just being a woman, minding my own business out here in these streets. Smh..I love you and I am so glad that you're ok!
✅Very interesting!

‼️Trigger Warning
This is the video Chicago Police refused to watch when I filed a complaint last summer after a man stalked me, publicly exposed himself, and verbally assaulted me (you can read the full story on @ihollagram, 🔗 in bio). Had they watched the video instead of telling me to get his name if I see him again (yes, an officer really said that to me), maybe it would not have taken THREE WEEKS for them to issue a Community Alert. 
I never shared this with anyone because in watching it back it looked scary to ME. But, y’all need to see this. This is an escalated version of what I deal with nearly every day. I wish I had videos of all the other micro-assaults: the cars slowing down, cars circling the block, the yelling, the leering, the following, all of it.

I’m beyond tired. But, I’m thinking every day of what I can do because this has got to get better for all of us. This is not a normal part of being a woman. This isn’t just mentally unstable men. This isn’t just happening at night. This isn’t just some men being “creepy.” This is assault. It is a crime.
#stopstreetharrassment #ProjectPleasurePrinciple #MeToo #protectblackwomen #youoksis
@lissahhb Not that I know of. It’s a hot mess out here.
@sandriawashington ugh. 🙏🙏🙏🙏

Holy shit. Did they ever arrest him? One of my favorite things is when they do stuff like "hey pretty lady" and then you ignore them and then get called all types of hoes and bitches. I mostly get called a fat bitch, but yeah.. SMH. This is so wrong and I wish there was a way to stop it.
@coachmekkalupuswarrior WOOOOW
@coachmekkalupuswarrior I can only imagine what women dealt with working inside of jails. That type of training is invaluable.
Wow. That's why I train My clients to be able to push People off them. That's crazy. I had to deal with that when I worked inside the jail. It was horrible. 🍆🍆🍆 every day.
@tarreytorae Every single time.
Oh My God! I’ve been harassed many times just like this. It is scary every time! I’m glad you are ok Sis
@mz_lott I hate that, too. We shouldn’t have to force ourselves to speak, change our route, etc.

This is so disturbing! Things could have gotten so much worse but you handled it. I don’t deal with this daily but there have definitely been some uncomfortable situations in the same vain. I hate the fact that sometimes I have to say hello just to avoid a potentially dangerous situation. 😕
Ohh wow sandie im so 😐
FYI: @blavity
@coachrobinrenee Thank you 🙏🏾
OMG!!! This is painful to watch,  knowing you have to endure these shenanigans. So sorry @sandriawashington
Wtf! Damn Sandy I hate this happened to you.
@brandy_kjr Thank you 🙏🏾🙏🏾
This was so hard to watch. I hate you have to go thru this. Keep recording and stay watchful Sandi and I pray Gods protection over you daily. 🙏🏾🤬🤬

@camillelaray That’s so scary. I’m sorry that happened. You’re right that we don’t stop to process how traumatic encounters like that are. We just keep it pushing...and expect that it’ll happen again. I’m glad you pepper sprayed that fool!! 🙌🏾

And honestly, I think these incidents happen so often to women that we don’t stop and properly tend to the trauma it causes. I had a dude harass and follow me 2 train line transfers then got off and started walking behind me. I pulled out my pepper spray, turned around and maced the shit outta of him. He went to his knees cussing and I just walked off and continued my day.
@darrylstreets1 I can’t be any safer
Be safe please

Ugh trigger warning is right?! I am so sorry this happened to you Sis and more than once?! Unacceptable on all levels. Continue to speak out. Continue to brave and courageous but most of all continue to pray and be safe! God bless you. And may God bless him. I hope one of his family members see this and gets him the help he needs. Keep smiling Sis! ❤️💯
Glad that things didn't escalate andvyour reporting it made tthe community aware. I was also saddened that the young man's behavior was disrespectful to you and other women he encountered. 😟

This video scared the crap out of me and made me relive some of the scary moments I was just discussing with a friend about some very similar personal experiences that I've dealt with just being a woman, minding my own business out here in these streets. Smh..I love you and I am so glad that you're ok!
✅Very interesting!
